<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
    <%= image_tag 'big_day_1.jpg', class: 'big_day_photo-right', align: 'right' %>
    <p>
      <h2>Ceremony</h2>
    </p>
    <h3>Location and Time:</h3>
    <p>Battery Gardens - Saturday May 28, 2016 at 5:30 pm</p>
    <h3>Attire:</h3>
    <p> Formal dress from either culture is appreciated. Battery Gardens’ outdoor patio can be susceptible to winds. A coat check will be provided. 
    </p>
    <p>
      Dr. Sanjib Mukherji, a friend of Asmita’s family for over 22 years, will officiate a traditional Vedic ceremony fused with American elements on the outdoor patio next to Battery Gardens. Similar to American culture, the wedding revolves around the tradition that the bride’s family is giving the bride away in marriage to the groom and that he is supposed to provide for her in the next phase of their life. Some parts of the ceremony will be spoken in Sanskrit to legitimize the union. The ceremony is anticipated to last an hour and will be moved indoors in case of inclement weather. 
    </p>
    <% if current_user.present? && [:asmita_family, :eric_family].include?(current_user.group_name) %>
    <p>
      Please join us for extended family pictures directly after the ceremony at the mandap (dais). The order will be as follows: Eric’s paternal family members, Eric’s entire family, Eric’s maternal family members, Asmita’s paternal family members, Asmita’s entire family, and Asmita’s maternal family members. 
    </p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- row image right -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
    <%= image_tag 'big_day_3.jpg', class: 'big_day_photo-left', align: 'left' %>
    <p>
      <h2>Reception</h2>
    </p>
    <p>
      Please join us for a cocktail reception with hors d'oeuvres in the Battery Gardens Fine Dining Room immediately following the ceremony. Dinner and dancing will follow upstairs in the Harbor View Room. Both events will feature New American cuisine with some Indian elements. Please note that there is no time to change attire between the ceremony and reception.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="small-12 large-12 columns">
    <%= image_tag 'big_day_2.jpg', class: 'big_day_photo-left', align: 'right' %>
